                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-42-defend487 t18230910-42-deflabel235"></join>; on the 14th of August, about half past seven o'clock in the morning, I left my watch in the privy, but did not miss it till half-past four o'clock in the afternoon; I immediately went to see if it was there, but it was gone; I went into the kitchen and asked her if she had seen it; she said No; next day, thinking she must know about it, I sent for an officer, and my wife searched her in the back parlour; it is worth 38 s.</p>
               <p>
            
